author: Samantha-Jo Roth
description: Democratic state Sen. Ghazala Hashmi made history Tuesday, defeating Republican radio host John Reid to become Virginia’s next lieutenant governor and the first Muslim woman ever elected to the post. The Associated Press called the race for Hashmi at 8:28 p.m. Tuesday. With 57% of the ballots counted, Hashmi led with 53.1% of the vote […]
title: Democratic state Sen. Ghazala Hashmi wins Virginia lieutenant governor race

description: President Donald Trump alleged that tens of thousands of Orthodox Jews turned out to vote for the Republican gubernatorial candidate for New Jersey, Jack Ciattarelli. “I just heard that 32,000 Orthodox Jews around Lakewood and Jackson, New Jersey, have showed up BIG for Jack Ciattarelli. title: Trump brags Orthodox Jews ‘showed up big’ for Ciattarelli

author: Mabinty Quarshie
description: Former Democratic Rep. Abigail Spanberger defeated Republican candidate Lt. Gov. Winsome Earle-Sears Tuesday night to become Virginia’s first female governor in the commonwealth’s history. The Associated Press called the race at 7:59 p.m., almost one hour after polls closed at 7:00 p.m. on Tuesday. Spanberger flipped the governor’s mansion blue four years after Gov. Glenn Youngkin (R-VA) won the […]
title: Spanberger delivers Democrats huge win in Virginia after defeating Earle-Sears for governorship

author: Brady Knox
description: The massacre that ensued after Rapid Support Forces took control of the Sudanese city of El Fasher is greater in scale than initially believed, with a top RSF commander estimating that at least 7,000 civilians were murdered. title: Top RSF commander estimates at least 7,000 civilians killed in El Fasher massacre in Sudan
